  "texts": [
    "For instance, the US NIH has an open call with $6m specifically for open-source development of AI drug design tools for Alzheimer's and related dementias, 108 the UK Research Ventures Catalyst gave £32m to companies developing training data assets and drug discovery models, 109 and Innovate UK funded an AI-enabled drug discovery consortium.",
    "110 Funding is often received through broader funding efforts rather than drug design-specific calls.",
    "Venture capital and legacy pharmaceutical investment in AI-enabled drug design is very strong and may outweigh government funding in its influence on the growth of these capabilities.",
    "Capabilities often remain proprietary.",
    "Examples include SandboxAQ, which raised $300m 111 for the development of AI models used primarily for drug design."
  ],
